# Runtime & environment

The scaffold reads env from `.env` at the repo root via `tsx --env-file=.env` (see `package.json` scripts). Source of truth: `.env.example`.

## Runtime selector

```
AGENT_RUNTIME=openai      # default — uses LLM_* below
AGENT_RUNTIME=codebuddy   # uses Tencent CodeBuddy SDK
```

`agentRuntime()` is exported from `shared/llm/src/index.ts`. Brains branch on it:

```ts
const runtime = agentRuntime();
if (runtime === "codebuddy") {
  return await codeBuddyChatJson(messages, OutputSchema, { maxTokens: 700 });
}
return await chatJson(messages, OutputSchema, { temperature: 0.3, maxTokens: 700 });
```

## OpenAI-compatible runtime

```
LLM_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
LLM_API_KEY=
LLM_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
```

Enforced cap: **30 calls per process** (`DAILY_CAP` in `shared/llm/src/index.ts`). On the 31st call, `RateLimitError` is thrown and brains fall back to `fallback.ts`.

## CodeBuddy runtime

```
CODEBUDDY_API_KEY=
CODEBUDDY_MODEL=default-model          # or gemini-3.1-pro / gpt-5.5 / kimi-k2.5 / etc.
CODEBUDDY_INTERNET_ENVIRONMENT=        # "" international, "internal" CN, "ioa" iOA
```

SDK: `@tencent-ai/agent-sdk@0.2.0`. The CLI ships inside `node_modules/@tencent-ai/agent-sdk/cli/bin/` — **no separate install needed**. Reference: `docs/codebuddy-docs/sdk.md`.

## Mock data endpoints

```
MOCK_TWITTER_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5599
MOCK_NEWS_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5599
MOCK_PRICES_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5599
MOCK_ONCHAIN_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5599
```

For local dev, all four point at the same Node mock server (`npm run mocks:serve`). On the workshop VM they're separate hostnames (`mock-*.foruai.io`).

## HTTP port

```
PORT=8080      # default for archetype A
```

Per-archetype convention: A=8080, B=8081, C=8082, D=8083, E=8084. Override with `PORT=...` when starting two archetypes side-by-side.

## Things CodeBuddy should NOT touch in .env

- **Do not commit `.env`** — it's in `.gitignore`. Suggest edits, never `git add .env`.
- **Do not echo `LLM_API_KEY` or `CODEBUDDY_API_KEY` values** into responses, commit messages, or logs.
